// Black Adam starts
#define RespondAbomination ["Does that creature truly believe it can command us?","Such primitive roars. It reminds me of the beasts I fought in the deserts of Kahndaq.","Do you hear that noise? It sounds like a child demanding attention.","His strength is undeniable, yet his technique is non-existent.","My patience has reached its limit. Shall we put him in the dirt?","A wrestling match? He mocks the concept of combat.","Even a monster should know when he is outclassed.","I find his posturing tedious."]

#define RespondKalEl ["He's looking for a fight. Should we oblige?","The Abomination is beneath my notice, though his arrogance is tiresome.","He’s calling us out, Adam. Are you going to answer?","I have no patience for his theatrics. If he wishes to die, I will grant him his wish.","He’s spoiling for a brawl. Any suggestions on how to handle him?","A quick strike to silence him permanently. It is the only language he understands.","Abomination! You are far from home. Stand down.","Waste no words on him, Kal-El. He is clearly incapable of complex thought.","He seems focused on you, Adam. Probably wants to prove he’s the strongest.","Then he will learn the truth of his own frailty soon enough.","You're awfully quiet, Adam. Waiting for the right moment?","I am waiting to see if he survives long enough to regret his challenge.","He’s definitely persistent. I’ll take the front, you flank him?","As you wish. Let us show this 'wrestling' champion what true power is."]
